The option to store Confluence attachments in WebDAV has never worked in a useful fashion, and has not been maintained for many versions. As such it is being EOL'd in Confluence 2.7.

Customers who store attachments in external WebDAV servers will need to migrate to filesystem or database-backed attachment storage BEFORE upgrading to Confluence 2.7

This DOES NOT affect the operation of the WebDAV plugin for Confluence.

